 pre-split, and the equivalent of $8 today.=0A=0A[7] This is, like, half of=
 the appeal of crypto to financial people: =E2=80=9CSmart =0Acontracts=E2=
=80=9D offer the possibility that the thing in the computer *is* the =0Acon=
tract, so there is no risk of translation error between them. (Though there=
 =0Ais always the risk of translation error in reducing the intended deal t=
o the =0Acontract/computer.)=0A=0A[8] Bizarrely, the company=E2=80=99s prox=
